msgctxt "0001"
msgid ""
"Would you like to study with me, Makoto? Just the two\n"
"of us?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0002"
msgid ""
"Come to my room! If there's anything you don't\n"
"understand, I'm a very attentive teacher!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0003"
msgid ""
"Um...I don't think I need you to be all that\n"
"attentive."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0004"
msgid "But sure, you don't mind if I stop by?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0005"
msgid "Of course not! Okay, let's do it!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0006"
msgid ""
"<CLT 4>With Taka leading the way, we headed to his room.\n"
"<CLT>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0007"
msgid ""
"Welcome, Makoto! You're the first guest I've invited\n"
"to my room!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0008"
msgid "Now that we're here, let me pose to you a question."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0009"
msgid "A question...?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0010"
msgid ""
"Don't worry, no studying required! This is the most\n"
"basic of basic questions. Very straightforward!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0011"
msgid ""
"Hahaha! This should be no challenge for you! Very\n"
"easy, I assure you!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0012"
msgid ""
"<CLT 4>Stop saying how easy it's gonna be. That just puts\n"
"even more pressure on me...\n"
"<CLT>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0013"
msgid ""
"Okay, here we go. What country first established\n"
"\"zero\" as a numerical concept?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0014"
msgid "India"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0015"
msgid "Japan"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0016"
msgid "Is it...Japan?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0017"
msgid "Wrong!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0018"
msgid "S-Sorry!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0019"
msgid "No, you don't have to apologize."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0020"
msgid ""
"<CLT 4>The way he reacted, I couldn't really help myself...\n"
"<CLT>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0021"
msgid ""
"But anyway, you're on the right track. It was an\n"
"Asian nation, I can tell you that much."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0022"
msgid "Greece"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0023"
msgid ""
"Could it be...Greece? I know they were famous for\n"
"philosophy, so..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0024"
msgid ""
"Come on, Makoto! Don't try to guess your way through\n"
"this!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0025"
msgid "S-Sorry..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0026"
msgid ""
"I'm sure you must have learned this at some point in\n"
"your education. Try to think back!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0027"
msgid "Come, now. It can't be that hard, can it?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0028"
msgid ""
"I'm sure you must have learned this at some point in\n"
"your education. Try to think back!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0029"
msgid ""
"<CLT 4>Hmm... Zero as a number, right? I'm pretty sure that\n"
"came from an Asian country...\n"
"<CLT>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0030"
msgid "It was...India, wasn't it?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0031"
msgid ""
"Correct! Good job, Makoto! I had faith in you,\n"
"and you came through for me!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0032"
msgid "Seeing you get excited is getting *me* excited!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0033"
msgid ""
"Let's stack our effort one on top of the other and\n"
"show those self-centered genius jerks what for!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0034"
msgid "Hey, um...Taka?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0035"
msgid "Yeah?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0036"
msgid ""
"Well, I've just noticed...you seem to really hate the\n"
"idea of geniuses."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0037"
msgid ""
"Hmm...I guess I feel like they're just...my sworn\n"
"enemy, you know?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0038"
msgid "Huh...?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0039"
msgid "But you hit the nail on the head. You're pretty sharp!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0040"
msgid "But...why?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0041"
msgid ""
"There's someone... Someone I respect, someone I hate.\n"
"Someone I have to surpass..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0042"
msgid "Because he was a genius."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0043"
msgid "What...?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0044"
msgid ""
"<CLT 3>Toranosuke Ishimaru<CLT>. Do you recognize that name?\n"
"...He was my grandfather."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0045"
msgid "He was once...Prime Minister of Japan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0046"
msgid "He was your grandpa!?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0047"
msgid ""
"He went from Minister of Foreign Affairs to Chief\n"
"Cabinet Secretary, and finally...Prime Minister."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0048"
msgid ""
"And all without any support network, and only a high\n"
"school degree...!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0049"
msgid ""
"He was, simply, a <CLT 3>genius<CLT>. Everything he did, he did\n"
"without any effort."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0050"
msgid ""
"He sounds like an amazing person. And he was your\n"
"grandfather?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0051"
msgid ""
"He was a genius. He'd never known failure. His success\n"
"was unimaginable to a normal person."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0052"
msgid "But because of that..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0053"
msgid ""
"...he allowed himself to be controlled by naive\n"
"emotions, and got roped into a corruption scandal."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0054"
msgid ""
"He had no idea what the world of geniuses was really\n"
"like. At least, that's how I see it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0055"
msgid "At that point, he fell just as fast as he had risen."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0056"
msgid ""
"And it wasn't just in politics. The business world\n"
"had no use for him anymore, and he plummeted."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0057"
msgid ""
"The debt he left behind torments my family to this\n"
"day."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0058"
msgid ""
"He died a few years ago. By the end, he wasn't\n"
"speaking to anyone."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0059"
msgid ""
"Despite his fame, his legacy...the only people who\n"
"came to his funeral were family members."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0060"
msgid "That's hard to imagine..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0061"
msgid ""
"Some consider genius fate's blessing. But I see it as\n"
"a tragedy more than anything."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0062"
msgid ""
"The tragedy of finding success without understanding\n"
"the importance of effort."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0063"
msgid ""
"There's nothing worse than a genius who trips and\n"
"falls."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0064"
msgid "Just like my grandfather..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0065"
msgid "And that's why you hate the word \"genius\"?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0066"
msgid ""
"My grandfather serves as an important lesson why you\n"
"must never be deceived by words like \"genius.\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0067"
msgid ""
"Relying on my own <CLT 3>effort<CLT>, I will reach greater\n"
"accomplishments than anything my grandfather ever did!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0068"
msgid ""
"So we have to work hard to build a society where those\n"
"who put in the most effort are properly rewarded!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0069"
msgid "I-I see..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0070"
msgid ""
"<CLT 4>I can agree with him, but Taka and I aren't the same.\n"
"I can't reach for those kinds of big dreams...\n"
"<CLT>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0071"
msgid "But you know, Makoto...I'm really happy!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0072"
msgid ""
"I figured this school would be full of geniuses. I\n"
"mean, I thought everyone would be my enemy."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0073"
msgid ""
"I never imagined I'd meet someone here who I could\n"
"share my story with..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0074"
msgid ""
"I'm so lucky to have met you here! This kind of thing\n"
"only happens once in a lifetime!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0075"
msgid ""
"I hope we can stay close, and combine our efforts to\n"
"shape things the way we want!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0076"
msgid "Yeah, definitely..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0077"
msgid "Okay, we have to keep on studying!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0078"
msgid ""
"<CLT 4>I feel like I've come to understand Taka a lot\n"
"better...\n"
"<CLT>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0079"
msgid ""
"<CLT 4>I think we've finally become <CLT><CLT 3>friends<CLT><CLT 4> in the truest\n"
"sense of the word.\n"
"<CLT>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0080"
msgid ""
"<CLT 23>Taka's <CLT><CLT 3>Report Card<CLT><CLT 23> has been updated based on your\n"
"experience with him.\n"
"<CLT>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0081"
msgid ""
"<CLT 23>Your maximum number of <CLT><CLT 3>Skill Points<CLT><CLT 23> has increased!\n"
"Hey, look at you go!\n"
"<CLT>"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "0082"
msgid ""
"<CLT 4>After lots of studying, I went back to my room.\n"
"<CLT>"
msgstr ""
